definition.value: A member of the class of dibenzothiazepines that is 3-chloro-6-methyl-6,11-dihydrodibenzo[c,f][1,2]thiazepine 5,5-dioxide substituted by a (6-carboxyhexyl)amino group at position 11.
A dimeric cyclohexadepsipeptide with formula C72H104N14O20. It is an antibiotic isolated from Streptomyces hygroscopicus and exhibits antitumor and antibacterial activity.
A composition-only glycan consisting of two acetaminohexosyl groups and one 6-deoxyhexosyl group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: HexNAc2 dHex1.
A composition-only glycan consisting of five hexosyl groups, three acetaminohexosyl groups and three 6-deoxyhexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex5 HexNAc3 dHex3.
A composition-only glycan consisting of four hexosyl groups, seven acetaminohexosyl groups and one 6-deoxyhexosyl group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex4 HexNAc7 dHex1.
